Sudetes requested a decision from the United States
In 1945, the Sudeten Germans requested the joining of the Bohmer forest to the United States.
This comes out of a letter stored in the collections of the South Bohemian Scientific Library.
If we cannot be part of Germany or Austria, we would like to live at least under the rule of the United States of America.
With such a desire, in 1945, some groups of Sudeten Germans have turned to the U.S. President.
This comes from, among other things, a letter retained in a private archive and today retained in the collections of the South Bohemian Scientific Library.
